Description: GeoMx ROI and Segment Metadata Attributes. The assayed biospecimen should be reported one per row with the associated ROI and AOI coordinates.
DependsOn: Component, NanoStringGeoMXROISegmentAnnotation_id, Biospecimen Key, GeoMx Scan name, GeoMx ROI Name, GeoMx AOI Name, GeoMx Tags, GeoMx ROI X Coordinate, GeoMx ROI Y Coordinate, GeoMx AOI X Coordinate, GeoMx AOI Y Coordinate, GeoMx QC status, GeoMx Scan Height, GeoMx Scan Width, GeoMx Scan Offset X, GeoMx Scan Offset Y, GeoMx Binding Density, GeoMx Positive norm factor, GeoMx Surface area, GeoMx Nuclei count, GeoMx Tissue Stain, GeoMx Slide name, NGS Raw reads, NGS Stitched reads, NGS Aligned reads, NGS Deduplicated reads, NGS Trimmed reads, NGS Sequencing Coverage, NGS MapQ30, GeoMx Negative count mean, GeoMx No Template Control count, GeoMx Excluded Outlier Probes, GeoMx Limit of Quantification

Description: Unique row identifier, used as a primary key for record updates
GeoMx Scan name (as appears in Segment Summary)
Name of Region of Interest corresponding to file. Multiple names should be comma-separated
Name of Area of Illumination corresponding to file. Multiple names should be comma-separated
Region of Interest X location within the image
Region of Interest Y location within the image
Area of Illumination X location within the image
Area of Illumination Y location within the image
ROI quality control flag as reported by the application
Height of the scan for GeoMx Analysis
Width of the scan for GeoMx Analysis
Offset X of the scan for GeoMx Analysis
Offset Y of the scan for GeoMx Analysis
The binding density as reported by the application
The Positive Control Normalization factor calculated using pos-hyb controls
Surface area of the ROI in square microns (Âµm2)
Number of nuclei detected in the segment (if applicable)
Similar to a Run ID, the slide name indicates the slide a given ROI is linked to (as reported in Segment Summary).
Is the median of all negative control probes for a given segment. A measure of signal to background for each segment.
Is the median count from all probes except the negative control probes. A measure of signal to background for each segment
The geometric mean of the unique negative probes in a GeoMx panel that do not target mRNA and establish the background count level per segment
The number of reads detected by the GeoMx probe panel in the control associated with this ROI.
The list of probes excluded from analysis.
The calculated limit of quantification associated with the segment.

The fraction of reads originating from an already-observed UMI. This is a function of library complexity and sequencing depth. More specifically, this is the fraction of confidently mapped, valid spot-barcode, valid UMI reads that had a non-unique (spot-barcode, UMI, gene).
